[b][size=3]How To Use[/size][/b]

[b]Automatic capture (no action needed):[/b]
[list]
[*][b]CTD:[/b] Dump + report are generated automatically when the game crashes
[*][b]Freeze / ILS:[/b] Helper auto-captures after a configurable time threshold
[/list]

[b]Manual snapshot:[/b]
Press [font=Courier New]Ctrl+Shift+F12[/font] while in-game to capture a snapshot on demand.
[i]Snapshots taken during normal gameplay may show "low confidence". Best used when the game is already stuck (freeze / ILS).[/i]

[b]Viewing results with the WinUI Viewer:[/b]
[list]
[*]After a CTD, the viewer may auto-open depending on your settings (see FAQ below)
[*]To open manually: drag & drop a [font=Courier New].dmp[/font] file onto [font=Courier New]SkyrimDiagDumpToolWinUI.exe[/font], then click "Analyze"
[*]Or run from command line: [font=Courier New]SkyrimDiagDumpToolWinUI.exe "path\to\dump.dmp"[/font]
[*]The viewer shows: Summary, Evidence list, Event timeline, Resource log, Wait Chain (WCT)
[/list]

[b]Where to find the viewer (MO2):[/b]
In MO2, right-click the mod → [b]Open in Explorer[/b], then navigate to:
[code]SKSE\Plugins\SkyrimDiagWinUI\SkyrimDiagDumpToolWinUI.exe[/code]
[i]Tip: Create a shortcut on your desktop for quick access.[/i]

[b][size=3]Capture Methods[/size][/b]
[code]
Situation              Dump pattern           Trigger
─────────────────────  ─────────────────────  ──────────────────────────
CTD (game crash)       *_Crash_*.dmp          Automatic
Freeze / ILS           *_Hang_*.dmp           Automatic (threshold)
Manual snapshot        *_Manual_*.dmp         Ctrl+Shift+F12
[/code]

[b][size=3]Output Location[/size][/b]
Default: MO2 [font=Courier New]overwrite\SKSE\Plugins\[/font]
Custom: set [font=Courier New]OutputDir=[/font] in [font=Courier New]SkyrimDiagHelper.ini[/font]

[b][size=3]Key Settings (SkyrimDiagHelper.ini)[/size][/b]
[code]
; Freeze/ILS detection thresholds (seconds)
HangThresholdInGameSec=15
HangThresholdLoadingSec=120
EnableAdaptiveLoadingThreshold=1    ; auto-learns loading times (recommended)

; Viewer auto-open behavior
AutoOpenViewerOnCrash=1             ; open viewer after CTD (1=on, 0=off)
AutoOpenCrashOnlyIfProcessExited=1  ; only open if game actually exited

; Disk cleanup (0 = unlimited)
MaxCrashDumps=10
MaxHangDumps=5
MaxManualDumps=5
[/code]

[b][size=3]Performance[/size][/b]
Designed with minimal overhead — event recording + on-demand dump capture, not continuous monitoring.
[list]
[*][font=Courier New]EnableResourceLog=1[/font] — hooks loose file opens (.nif/.hkx/.tri). Disable first ([font=Courier New]=0[/font]) if you suspect overhead.
[*][font=Courier New]EnablePerfHitchLog=1[/font] — logs main-thread stalls (lightweight).
[*][font=Courier New]CrashHookMode=1[/font] — keep at 1. Mode 2 (all exceptions) is not recommended.
[/list]

[b][size=3]Language[/size][/b]
UI follows your Windows language by default. Override:
[code]
SkyrimDiagDumpToolWinUI.exe --lang en
SkyrimDiagDumpToolWinUI.exe --lang ko
[/code]

[b][size=3]FAQ[/size][/b]

[b]Q: The viewer popped up during save/load but the game kept running?[/b]
A: An exception during save/cosave may be internally handled — the game can continue. The "likely cause" shown is a [i]warning signal[/i], not a confirmed crash cause. To reduce popups, set [font=Courier New]AutoOpenCrashOnlyIfProcessExited=1[/font] (default) or [font=Courier New]AutoOpenViewerOnCrash=0[/font].

[b]Q: Where are the dump files?[/b]
A: By default under MO2 [font=Courier New]overwrite\SKSE\Plugins\[/font]. Set [font=Courier New]OutputDir=[/font] in [font=Courier New]SkyrimDiagHelper.ini[/font] to collect everything in one folder.

[b]Q: Do I need CrashLoggerSSE?[/b]
A: Not required, but recommended. When installed, Tullius auto-detects and includes CrashLogger's output for richer diagnostics.

[b][size=3]Privacy[/size][/b]
[list]
[*]Dumps may contain local file paths and usernames
[*]Review/mask before sharing publicly
[*]Analysis results are best-effort estimates (shown with Confidence level)
[/list]

[b][size=3]Support[/size][/b]
When reporting issues, please include:
[list]
[*]The [font=Courier New].dmp[/font] file
[*]Matching report outputs: [font=Courier New]*_SkyrimDiagReport.txt[/font], [font=Courier New]*_SkyrimDiagSummary.json[/font]
[*](if available) [font=Courier New]SkyrimDiag_Incident_*.json[/font], [font=Courier New]*_SkyrimDiagBlackbox.jsonl[/font], CrashLogger logs
[/list]

